JD - 1 :

What You'll Do :
Client Communications & Strategy
- Build strong relationships with clients and align PR campaigns to business goals
- Develop integrated media strategies and communication plans
- Lead the charge on client servicing, reporting, and stakeholder management

Press & Media Relations
- Pitch stories, interviews, and op-eds to top-tier business and lifestyle journalists
- Maintain relationships with editors, reporters, digital creators & influencers
- Secure impactful coverage across mainstream and digital publications

Content & Campaign Execution
- Draft press releases, thought leadership articles, media kits, and pitch notes
- Align content with brand voice and campaign objectives
- Leverage tools like PR Newswire, Meltwater, Wizikey, etc. for media outreach

Media Monitoring & Analytics
- Monitor coverage, industry news, and campaign performance
- Share of Voice (SOV), sentiment analysis, and campaign reporting

What We are Looking For
- 1+ years in a PR agency (preferred sectors: lifestyle, tech, business, or consumer)
- Proven ability to manage clients, craft pitches, and deliver measurable PR results
- Robust media network—feature writers, editors, digital creators, etc.
- Excellent command over written and verbal communication
- Detail-oriented, creative thinker, and deadline-driven

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

JD - 2 :

Responsibilities for Account Manager

- build solid relationships and networks with colleagues, clients and the media
- monitor the media, including newspapers, magazines, journals, broadcasts, newswires, social media sites and blogs, for opportunities for clients
- work as part of an account team to develop client proposals and implement the PR activity
- prepare regular client reports and attend client meetings
- research, write and distribute press releases to targeted media
- promote news stories and features to the media
- collate, analyse and evaluate media coverage
- manage events, including press conferences and promotional events

