JD - 3 :

Key Responsibilities
• Develop and execute the annual PR & communications strategy for couture, prêt, and collaborations.
• Build strong relationships with fashion editors, journalists, stylists, influencers, and celebrities.
• Oversee celebrity dressing opportunities, ensuring placements align with brand values.
• Lead brand/cultural collaborations (luxury hotels, art institutions, stylists, curated projects).
• Craft and oversee press releases, interviews, press kits, and media notes.
• Manage PR agencies and ensure deliverables are on brand.
• Crisis communications management to safeguard reputation.
• Monitor and report press outcomes, media value, and collaboration ROI.

Skills & Qualifications
• 7–8 years in luxury PR, ideally with fashion/lifestyle exposure.
• Strong media network (India & international).
• Confident leader with excellent communication skills.
• Strategic yet hands-on in execution.

